mib3.name: mib3

revisions.description: monitor HubMode added SFP warnings and alarms added
syslog filtering added snmpv3 specific traps/informs added
port access control values added radius timeout added
Special purpose Vlan IDs Storage Media Card Support Inventory string
Ring Notifications implemented reduced line length (to avoid HPOV-Bug)

deviceArtNo.name: deviceArtNo
deviceArtNo.description: This entry describes the article number of the device.

deviceSerNo.name: deviceSerNo
deviceSerNo.description: This entry describes the serial number of the device.

deviceHardware.name: deviceHardware
deviceHardware.description: This entry contains the hardware version of the device.

deviceDescription.name: deviceDescription
deviceDescription.description: This entry contains a description of the device.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: This entry contains a description of the device.

deviceLocation.name: deviceLocation
deviceLocation.description: This entry contains the location of the device.

deviceContact.name: deviceContact
deviceContact.description: This entry contains a contact regarding the device.

deviceGroup.name: deviceGroup
deviceGroup.description: This entry defines the name of the group the device belongs to.

deviceTemperature.name: deviceTemperature
deviceTemperature.description: This is the current temperature of the device in degree celsius. A value of 255 has to be interpreted as 'unsupported'.

deviceTemperatureLevel.name: deviceTemperatureLevel
deviceTemperatureLevel.description: This is the current temperature level of the device.

deviceUpTime.name: deviceUpTime
deviceUpTime.description: Time since the device was last re-initialized (in 0.01s).

deviceFddActiveTime.name: deviceFddActiveTime
deviceFddActiveTime.description: Active Time interval for Fibre- Down-Detection Feature (in 0.01s). valid range: [10 .. 100000] A value of '0' means 'unsupported'

deviceFddPassiveTime.name: deviceFddPassiveTime
deviceFddPassiveTime.description: Passive Time interval for Fibre- Down-Detection Feature (in 0.01s). valid range: [10 .. 100000] A value of '0' means 'unsupported'

deviceInventory.name: deviceInventory
deviceInventory.description: This entry contains an inventory string for the device.

agentFirmware.name: agentFirmware
agentFirmware.description: This entry contains the firmware version of the agent.

agentMacAddress.name: agentMacAddress
agentMacAddress.description: This entry contains the mac address of the agent.

agentIpMode.name: agentIpMode
agentIpMode.description: This entry describes the IP-mode of the agent.

agentIpAddress.name: agentIpAddress
agentIpAddress.description: This entry contains the IP-address of the agent.

agentSubnetMask.name: agentSubnetMask
agentSubnetMask.description: This entry contains the subnet mask of the agent.

agentGateway.name: agentGateway
agentGateway.description: This entry contains the gateway ip address for the agent.

agentConfigReset.name: agentConfigReset
agentConfigReset.description: Set this entry to '1' to reset the device. This entry is self clearing.

agentConfigFactoryDefault.name: agentConfigFactoryDefault
agentConfigFactoryDefault.description: Set this entry to '1' before setting the entry 'agentConfigReset' to '1' sets the device to factory defaults once and the entry is self cleared. Setting this entry to '2' it will remain as set and every standard reset will be a factory reset. If 'Permanent Factory Reset' is not supported then the 'Temporary Factory Reset' will be set instead.

agentConfigEnableFactoryButton.name: agentConfigEnableFactoryButton
agentConfigEnableFactoryButton.description: Setting this entry to a '1' enables the hardware button for a factory reset if available.

agentSecureAddressFlag.name: agentSecureAddressFlag
agentSecureAddressFlag.description: This Entry documents the Flag which is set from the system if invalid values for MAC-address, IP-address or subnet mask have been found in the stored configuration. In this case hard coded secure values are used instead of those found. This flag is cleared if valid valued are found when the system comes up.

agentStorageMediaCardStatus.name: agentStorageMediaCardStatus
agentStorageMediaCardStatus.description: This Entry represents the detected status of a storage memory card if supported.

agentStorageMediaCardBoot.name: agentStorageMediaCardBoot
agentStorageMediaCardBoot.description: Set this entry to '1' before setting the entry 'agentConfigReset' to '1' sets the device's config to the values stored on the Storage Media Card once if available . and the entry is self cleared. Setting this entry to '2' it will remain as set and every boot event will use the configuration from the card. If not supported a value of 255 will be returned.

agentStorageMediaCardMac.name: agentStorageMediaCardMac
agentStorageMediaCardMac.description: Set this entry to '1' before setting the entry 'agentConfigReset' to '1' leads to take the MAC address from the SMC. Be very careful with this service option to avoid duplicated MAC addresses.!

agentStoreConfigToStorageMediaCard.name: agentStoreConfigToStorageMediaCard
agentStoreConfigToStorageMediaCard.description: Set this entry to '1' to store the present configuration to the storage media card if available. This entry is self clearing.

portCount.name: portCount
portCount.description: The number of ports resent on this system.

portStatusTable.name: portStatusTable
portStatusTable.description: This table contains port status information of the device.

portStatusTableEntry.name: portStatusTableEntry
portStatusTableEntry.description: Entry in the port status table.

portStatusId.name: portStatusId
portStatusId.description: This entry describes the port id.

portStatusType.name: portStatusType
portStatusType.description: This entry describes the type of the port.

portStatusLink.name: portStatusLink
portStatusLink.description: This entry describes the link status of the port.

portStatusSpeed.name: portStatusSpeed
portStatusSpeed.description: This entry describes the current speed status of the port if available.

portStatusDuplex.name: portStatusDuplex
portStatusDuplex.description: This entry describes the current duplex status of the port if available.

portStatusFlowControl.name: portStatusFlowControl
portStatusFlowControl.description: This entry describes the current flow control status of the port if available. This state referres the current duplex mode.

portStatusPinout.name: portStatusPinout
portStatusPinout.description: This entry describes the current pinout status of the port if available.

portStatusFarEndFault.name: portStatusFarEndFault
portStatusFarEndFault.description: This entry describes the current Far End Fault Detection status of the port if available.

portStatusRxNetload.name: portStatusRxNetload
portStatusRxNetload.description: This entry describes the receiver netload in percent, adapted to the selected port speed. Netload values greater than '0' but less that '1' are rounded up to a '1' to differentiate them from real zero-values. If netload measuring is not supported, then a value of '-1' is given back.

portStatusTxNetload.name: portStatusTxNetload
portStatusTxNetload.description: This entry describes the transmitter netload in percent, adapted to the selected port speed. Netload values greater than '0' but less that '1' are rounded up to a '1' to differentiate them from real zero-values. If netload measuring is not supported, then a value of '-1' is given back.

portConfigTable.name: portConfigTable
portConfigTable.description: This table contains the port configuration of the device.

portConfigTableEntry.name: portConfigTableEntry
portConfigTableEntry.description: Entry in the port configuration table.

portConfigId.name: portConfigId
portConfigId.description: This entry describes the device's port id.

portConfigAlias.name: portConfigAlias
portConfigAlias.description: This entry contains an individual name for the port.

portConfigEnable.name: portConfigEnable
portConfigEnable.description: This entry describes the type of the port.

portConfigAutonego.name: portConfigAutonego
portConfigAutonego.description: This entry describes the current autonegotiation configuration of the port if available.

portConfigSpeed.name: portConfigSpeed
portConfigSpeed.description: This entry describes the current speed configuration of the port if available. This entry is only valid if Autonegotiation is disabled.

portConfigDuplex.name: portConfigDuplex
portConfigDuplex.description: This entry describes the current duplex configuration of the port if available. This entry is only valid if Autonegotiation is disabled.

portConfigFlowControl.name: portConfigFlowControl
portConfigFlowControl.description: This entry describes the current flow control configuration of the port if available. The current duplex mode is is used to to select the matching settings. This entry is used for advertising if Autonegotiation is enabled and for forcing if AN is disabled.

portConfigPinout.name: portConfigPinout
portConfigPinout.description: This entry describes the current pinout configuration of a copper port if available.

portConfigFarEndFault.name: portConfigFarEndFault
portConfigFarEndFault.description: This entry describes the current far end fault behaviour of a fiber port if available.

portConfigAdvertise.name: portConfigAdvertise
portConfigAdvertise.description: This entry describes the autonegotiation advertise information of the port.

portConfigFibreDownDetection.name: portConfigFibreDownDetection
portConfigFibreDownDetection.description: This entry describes the current fibre down detection behaviour of a fiber port if available.

vlanEnable.name: vlanEnable
vlanEnable.description: This entry enables or disables vlan filtering.

vlanForceDefaultVID.name: vlanForceDefaultVID
vlanForceDefaultVID.description: This entry enables or disables forcing default vlan id.

vlanFilterCount.name: vlanFilterCount
vlanFilterCount.description: This entry describes the number of supported vlan filters.

vlanVoiceVID.name: vlanVoiceVID
vlanVoiceVID.description: This entry describes the default VID for Voice over IP operation. This VID is communicated via CDP and LLDP.

vlanRstpVID.name: vlanRstpVID

vlanUnauthVID.name: vlanUnauthVID

vlanPortMode.description: This entry describes the vlan mode the port.

vlanDefaultVID.name: vlanDefaultVID
vlanDefaultVID.description: This entry describes default vid for the port.

vlanDefaultPriority.name: vlanDefaultPriority
vlanDefaultPriority.description: This entry describes default priority tag for the port.

vlanPortFlags.name: vlanPortFlags
vlanPortFlags.description: This Entry contains per port some bitwise filter settings: Bit 0: Force Port Default VID (only valid if vlanForceDefaultVID is set to '3') Bit 1: per VID Priority Override

vlanFilterEnhTable.name: vlanFilterEnhTable
vlanFilterEnhTable.description: This table contains the enhanced vlan filter configuration.

vlanFilterEnhTableEntry.name: vlanFilterEnhTableEntry
vlanFilterEnhTableEntry.description: Entry in the vlan filter enhanced configuration table.

vlanFilterEnhId.name: vlanFilterEnhId
vlanFilterEnhId.description: This entry contains the filter id for the enhanced vlan filter table.

vlanFilterEnhFlags.name: vlanFilterEnhFlags
vlanFilterEnhFlags.description: This Entry contains some flags for VLAN filter settings. The content is defined as following: Bit 0: Filter Enabled Bit 1: per VID Priority Override Enabled

vlanFilterEnhPriOverride.name: vlanFilterEnhPriOverride
vlanFilterEnhPriOverride.description: This entry contains the priority value to override an ingress frame with if its VLAN ID fits, filtering is enabled, port selective override flag is set and filter selective override flag is set.

prioSupport.name: prioSupport
prioSupport.description: This entry contains the information if prioritization is supported or not.

prioQueueCount.name: prioQueueCount
prioQueueCount.description: This entry defines the number of queues supported by the device.

prioQueueScheme.name: prioQueueScheme
prioQueueScheme.description: This entry defines the queue scheme for prioritization.

prioPortEnable.name: prioPortEnable
prioPortEnable.description: Hardwaret prioritization of the device is applied if all other type of prioritization are not applicable.

prioIeeeTagEnable.name: prioIeeeTagEnable
prioIeeeTagEnable.description: If enabled, a IEEE 802.1p tagged frame will be mapped to the queue that is assigned to this tag

prioDiffservEnable.name: prioDiffservEnable
prioDiffservEnable.description: If enabled a tagged frame will be mapped to the queue that is assigned to this tag.

prioPortTable.name: prioPortTable
prioPortTable.description: This table contains the port prioritization of the device. This setting is always valid if no other type of prioritization has been selected.

prioPortTableEntry.name: prioPortTableEntry
prioPortTableEntry.description: Entry in the port prioritization table.

prioPortId.name: prioPortId
prioPortId.description: This entry describes the device's port id.

prioPortQueue.name: prioPortQueue
prioPortQueue.description: This entry describes the selected queue if port prioritization is available.

prioIeeeTagTable.name: prioIeeeTagTable
prioIeeeTagTable.description: This table contains the configuuration of IEEE 802.1p prioritization. Each of the 8 different values is assigned to one of the available queues here.

prioIeeeTagTableEntry.name: prioIeeeTagTableEntry
prioIeeeTagTableEntry.description: Entry in the IEEE 802.1p tag prioritization table.

prioIeeeTagId.name: prioIeeeTagId
prioIeeeTagId.description: This entry defines the IEEE 802.1p tag a queue is assigned to.

prioIeeeTagQueue.name: prioIeeeTagQueue
prioIeeeTagQueue.description: This entry describes the selected queue for each IEEE 802.1p tag.

prioDiffservTable.name: prioDiffservTable
prioDiffservTable.description: This table contains the configuuration of DiffServ prioritization. Each of the 64 different values is assigned to one of the available queues here.

prioDiffservTableEntry.name: prioDiffservTableEntry
prioDiffservTableEntry.description: Entry in the Diffserv prioritization table.

prioDiffservId.name: prioDiffservId
prioDiffservId.description: This entry defines the Diffserv index a queue is assigned to.

prioDiffservQueue.name: prioDiffservQueue
prioDiffservQueue.description: This entry describes the selected queue for each Diffserv index.

monitorSupport.name: monitorSupport
monitorSupport.description: This entry contains the information if port monitoring is supported or not.

monitorMode.name: monitorMode
monitorMode.description: This entry enables or disables monitoring and selects the mode of operation.

monitorSource.name: monitorSource
monitorSource.description: This entry contains the monitor source portnumber.

monitorDestination.name: monitorDestination
monitorDestination.description: This entry contains the monitor destination portnumber.

ringSupport.name: ringSupport
ringSupport.description: This entry contains the information if ethernet ring feature is supported or not.

ringCount.name: ringCount
ringCount.description: The number of supported rings on this system.

ringTable.name: ringTable
ringTable.description: This table contains the ring configuration of the device.

ringTableEntry.name: ringTableEntry
ringTableEntry.description: Entry in the ring configuration table.

ringId.name: ringId
ringId.description: This entry describes the ring id.

ringMode.name: ringMode
ringMode.description: This entry enables or disables ring mode and selects the mode of operation.

ringPortA.name: ringPortA
ringPortA.description: This entry defines port A for the ring function. If the device is a 'master' this is the main port. If ring feature is not supported a 255 will be replied.

ringPortB.name: ringPortB
ringPortB.description: This entry defines port B for the ring function. If the device is a 'master' this is the backup port. If ring feature is not supported a 255 will be replied.

ringNumber.name: ringNumber
ringNumber.description: This entry defines the ring ID number. If ring feature is not supported a 255 will be replied.

ringStatus.name: ringStatus
ringStatus.description: This entry defines the ring status.

ringAlarmDuration.name: ringAlarmDuration
ringAlarmDuration.description: Duration of ring alarm status (in 0.01s). This entry is used as additional status information in repeated ring alarm traps if error status remains unchanged. A value of '0' means 'no ring alarm'

couplingredSupport.name: couplingredSupport
couplingredSupport.description: This entry contains the information if ring coupling redundancy is supported or not.

couplingredPort.name: couplingredPort
couplingredPort.description: This entry defines the port for the ring coupling redundancy function. If not supported this entry is set to 0.

couplingredMode.name: couplingredMode
couplingredMode.description: This entry enables or disables ring coupling redundancy mode and selects the mode of operation.

couplingredPartnerIp.name: couplingredPartnerIp
couplingredPartnerIp.description: This entry defines the ip address of the ring coupling redundancy partner. In backup mode this is the ip address of the main device. In main mode this is the ip address of the backup device. If not supported this entry is set to 0.0.0.0 .

couplingredStatus.name: couplingredStatus
couplingredStatus.description: This entry defines the ring coupling redundancy mode status.

couplingredPartnerStatus.name: couplingredPartnerStatus
couplingredPartnerStatus.description: This entry defines the ring coupling redundancy mode status.

couplingredValidationFlag.name: couplingredValidationFlag
couplingredValidationFlag.description: This entry defines the validation of ring coupling redundancy. Bit 0 indicates a valid configuration, Bit 1 indicates a valid status. If ring coupling redundancy is unsupported or disabled this entry is set to 255.

sfpSupport.name: sfpSupport
sfpSupport.description: This entry contains the information if sfp modules are supported or not.

sfpCount.name: sfpCount
sfpCount.description: The number of supported sfp modules.

sfpTable.name: sfpTable
sfpTable.description: This table contains the sfp module status of the device.

sfpTableEntry.name: sfpTableEntry
sfpTableEntry.description: Entry in the sfp status table.

sfpId.name: sfpId
sfpId.description: This entry describes the sfp id.

sfpPortnumber.name: sfpPortnumber
sfpPortnumber.description: This entry describes the number of the port where the sfp can be plugged in.

sfpDetect.name: sfpDetect
sfpDetect.description: This entry enables or disables uplink redundancy

sfpVendor.name: sfpVendor
sfpVendor.description: This entry describes the vendor name of the sfp.

sfpVendorPartnumber.name: sfpVendorPartnumber
sfpVendorPartnumber.description: This entry describes the vendor partnumber of the sfp.

sfpVendorSerialnumber.name: sfpVendorSerialnumber
sfpVendorSerialnumber.description: This entry describes the vendor serialnumber of the sfp.

sfpConnector.name: sfpConnector
sfpConnector.description: This entry describes the type of connector of the sfp.

sfpNominalBitrate.name: sfpNominalBitrate
sfpNominalBitrate.description: This entry describes the nominal bitrate of the sfp. It is a maximum value, a lower value may be used instead.

sfpDiagnostic.name: sfpDiagnostic
sfpDiagnostic.description: This entry describes tha avalability and type of diagnostics.

sfpTemperature.name: sfpTemperature
sfpTemperature.description: This entry describes the temperature of the sfp in multiple of 0.1 degree celsius.

sfpVoltage.name: sfpVoltage
sfpVoltage.description: This entry describes the supply voltage of the sfp in multiple of 0.01 V.

sfpTxBias.name: sfpTxBias
sfpTxBias.description: This entry describes the transmit bias current of the sfp in multiple of 0.01 mA.

sfpTxPower.name: sfpTxPower
sfpTxPower.description: This entry describes the optical transmit power of the sfp in multiple of 0.1 uW.

sfpRxPower.name: sfpRxPower
sfpRxPower.description: This entry describes the ooptical receive power of the sfp in multiple of 0.1 uW.

sfpWarnings.name: sfpWarnings
sfpWarnings.description: This entry contains the flags for internal warnings. A warning occurrs if regarding warning threshold is exceeded.

sfpAlarms.name: sfpAlarms
sfpAlarms.description: This entry contains the flags for internal alarms. An alarm occurrs if regarding alarm threshold is exceeded.

relaisSupport.name: relaisSupport
relaisSupport.description: This entry contains the information if an alram relais is supported or not.

relaisCount.name: relaisCount
relaisCount.description: The number of supported relais on this system.

relaisTable.name: relaisTable
relaisTable.description: This table contains the relais configuration of the device.

relaisTableEntry.name: relaisTableEntry
relaisTableEntry.description: Entry in the relais configuration table.

relaisId.name: relaisId
relaisId.description: This entry describes the relais id.

relaisAlias.name: relaisAlias
relaisAlias.description: This entry contains an individual name for the relais.

relaisMode.name: relaisMode
relaisMode.description: This entry describes the bahaviour of the alarm relais.

relaisStatus.name: relaisStatus
relaisStatus.description: This entry describes the present status of the alarm relais.

pacSupport.name: pacSupport
pacSupport.description: This entry contains the information if port authentication is supported or not.

pacEnable.name: pacEnable
pacEnable.description: This entry enables or disables port authentication.

pacUnauthMode.name: pacUnauthMode
pacUnauthMode.description: The entry describes the mode of operation for unauthorized ports.

pacUnauthVID.name: pacUnauthVID
pacUnauthVID.description: This entry describes the default VID for ports which are unauthorized.

pacMaxNumberOfAllowedHostsPerPort.name: pacMaxNumberOfAllowedHostsPerPort
pacMaxNumberOfAllowedHostsPerPort.description: The value contains the maximum number of supported Hosts per port of this device.

pacFallbackRequestEnable.name: pacFallbackRequestEnable
pacFallbackRequestEnable.description: This entry describes if authentication method fallback to MAC authentication after a request timeout is enabled(1) or not(2)

pacFallbackRequestTimeout.name: pacFallbackRequestTimeout
pacFallbackRequestTimeout.description: This entry contains the timeout value in seconds. If no response to a 802.1X request has been detected after this time a fallback to MAC authentication occures if bit 0 of pacFallbackMode is set.

pacFallbackRejectsEnable.name: pacFallbackRejectsEnable
pacFallbackRejectsEnable.description: This entry describes if authentication method fallback to MAC authentication after a limited number of rejects is enabled(1) or not(2)

pacFallbackMaxRejects.name: pacFallbackMaxRejects
pacFallbackMaxRejects.description: This entry contains the maximum number of rejects by the Radius server. If this number is achieved a fallback to MAC authentication occures if bit 1 of pacFallbackMode is set.

pacSupplicantTimeout.name: pacSupplicantTimeout
pacSupplicantTimeout.description: This entry contains the Supplicant timeout value in seconds.

pacReauthEnable.name: pacReauthEnable
pacReauthEnable.description: This entry describes if reauthentication after a configured time will be done(1) not(2).

pacReauthTime.name: pacReauthTime
pacReauthTime.description: This entry contains the reauthentication time period in minutes.

pacStatusTable.name: pacStatusTable
pacStatusTable.description: This table contains the port status of the port access control feature.

pacStatusTableEntry.name: pacStatusTableEntry
pacStatusTableEntry.description: Entry in the port access control port status table.

pacStatPortId.name: pacStatPortId
pacStatPortId.description: This entry describes the port id.

pacStatPortMode.name: pacStatPortMode
pacStatPortMode.description: This entry describes the port access control mode.

pacStatPortStatus.name: pacStatPortStatus
pacStatPortStatus.description: This entry describes the port access control status.

pacStatUserStatus1.name: pacStatUserStatus1
pacStatUserStatus1.description: This entry describes the port access control mode status for the first host. Note, that different states of several authentication methods are summarized here. They are marked with different multiples of ten as an offset for each mode.

pacStatUserStatus2.name: pacStatUserStatus2
pacStatUserStatus2.description: This entry describes the port access control mode status for the second host. Note, that different states of several authentication methods are summarized here. They are marked with different multiples of ten as an offset for each mode.

pacStatUserStatus3.name: pacStatUserStatus3
pacStatUserStatus3.description: This entry describes the port access control mode status for the third host. Note, that different states of several authentication methods are summarized here. They are marked with different multiples of ten as an offset for each mode.

pacStatUserStatus4.name: pacStatUserStatus4
pacStatUserStatus4.description: This entry describes the port access control mode status for the fourth host. Note, that different states of several authentication methods are summarized here. They are marked with different multiples of ten as an offset for each mode.

pacStatUserMac1.name: pacStatUserMac1
pacStatUserMac1.description: This entry contains the 1st host mac address at the selected port if available.

pacStatUserMac2.name: pacStatUserMac2
pacStatUserMac2.description: This entry contains the 2nd host mac address at the selected port if available.

pacStatUserMac3.name: pacStatUserMac3
pacStatUserMac3.description: This entry contains the 3rd host mac address at the selected port if available.

pacStatUserMac4.name: pacStatUserMac4
pacStatUserMac4.description: This entry contains the 4th host mac address at the selected port if available.

pacStatUserName1.name: pacStatUserName1
pacStatUserName1.description: This entry contains the 1st host user name at the selected port if available.

pacStatUserName2.name: pacStatUserName2

rtcFlags.description: This Entry contains per port some bitwise rtc settings: Bit 0: if set rtc should be synchronized with configured SNTP server Bit 1: is set if DST support is enabled

rtcLocalTime.name: rtcLocalTime
rtcLocalTime.description: This entry contains the local date and time information. Used format conforms to RFC2068 like example below: Mon Jun 21 17:20:34 2010

rtcManualTime.name: rtcManualTime
rtcManualTime.description: On readout this entry contains the local date and time information. Writing to this entry sets the the date and time information of the device manually. Used format is 'DD.MM.YYYY HH:MM:SS'

rtcTimeStatus.name: rtcTimeStatus
rtcTimeStatus.description: This entry contains the information about the reliability of the date and time information of the device.

rtcTimezoneOffset.name: rtcTimezoneOffset
rtcTimezoneOffset.description: This entry describes the time offset to UTC regarding the timezone of the device. The units of this entry are multiples of 30 minutes.

rtcDSTOffset.name: rtcDSTOffset
rtcDSTOffset.description: This entry describes the time offset to UTC regarding the timezone of the device. This entry is measured in minutes.

rtcDSTbegin.name: rtcDSTbegin
rtcDSTbegin.description: This entry contains the hexadecimal represenation of the proprietary coded time of the beginning of DST period. See corresponding feature description for detailed information.

rtcDSTend.name: rtcDSTend
rtcDSTend.description: This entry contains the hexadecimal represenation of the proprietary coded time of the end of DST period. See corresponding feature description for detailed information.

rtcDSTstatus.name: rtcDSTstatus
rtcDSTstatus.description: If DST support is enabled this entry contains the information if DST period is active now(1) or not(2). Else a value of 255 will be read out.

rtcSNTPsyncInterval.name: rtcSNTPsyncInterval
rtcSNTPsyncInterval.description: This entry describes the time interval for repeated to synchronisation of the device with a given SNTP server if this feature is enabled. This value is measured in minutes. It should not be set too small to avoid server overload in larger networks. A typical value should be 10080 which represents once a week.

rtcSNTPsyncNow.name: rtcSNTPsyncNow
rtcSNTPsyncNow.description: Set this entry to '1' to trigger a rtc sychronisation with SNTP server now. This entry is self clearing.

rtcSNTPServerCount.name: rtcSNTPServerCount

rtcSNTPServerId.description: This entry contains the SNTP server ID.

rtcSNTPServerStatus.name: rtcSNTPServerStatus
rtcSNTPServerStatus.description: This entry describes the SNTP server status as retransmitted after sync.

rtcSNTPServerIpAddress.name: rtcSNTPServerIpAddress

consoleSupport.name: consoleSupport
consoleSupport.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which console version is supported. Bit 0: Telnet supported Bit 1: SSH supported

consoleEnable.name: consoleEnable
consoleEnable.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which console version is enabled. Bit 0: Telnet enabled Bit 1: SSH enabled Changing this entry takes effect after reset.

consoleTimeout.name: consoleTimeout
consoleTimeout.description: This entry describes the timout value in multiples of a second. This is the period of inactivity after which the telnet connection shuts down automatically.

consoleApplyMode.name: consoleApplyMode
consoleApplyMode.description: If this entry is set to '1' changes due to 'set...' commands are immediately applied to the switch and saved in the configuration. If it is set to '2' changes are also applied immediately but the changed configuration will not be saved. If it is set to '3' changes are neither applied to the switch nor the configuration is saved. Using the 'save settings' command at the telnet console the configuration will be applied and saved. After a reset this value is always set to the default value of 2 (saveManually).

consolePrompt.name: consolePrompt
consolePrompt.description: This is the string used as prompt for the telnet console.

webSupport.name: webSupport
webSupport.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which web interface version is supported. Bit 0: HTTP supported Bit 1: HTTPS supported

webEnable.name: webEnable
webEnable.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which web interface version is enabled. Bit 0: HTTP enabled Bit 1: HTTPS enabled Changing this entry takes effect after reset.

snmpSupport.name: snmpSupport
snmpSupport.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which SNMP version is supported. Bit 0: SNMP v1 supported Bit 1: SNMP v2c supported Bit 2: SNMP v3 supported

snmpEnable.name: snmpEnable
snmpEnable.description: This entry contains the bitwise information which SNMP version is enabled. Bit 0: SNMP v1 enabled Bit 1: SNMP v2c enabled Bit 2: SNMP v3 enabled It is not allowed to disable an interface via itself or to support v1/v2c at the same time as v3 is enabled. So v1 or v2c can only be enabled via this entry if v3 is disabled. Further changes have to be done via another Interface.

snmpApplyMode.name: snmpApplyMode
snmpApplyMode.description: If this entry is set to '1' changes due to 'set...' commands are immediately applied to the switch and saved in the configuration. If it is set to '2' changed are also applied immedately but the changed configuration will not be saved. So changes are lost after a reset. To save the configuration an additional self clearing 'snmpApply' has to be set to '1' for an apply without save or set to '2' for an apply including save. After a reset this value is always set to the default value of 1 (applyAndSaveImmediately).

snmpApply.name: snmpApply
snmpApply.description: This entry only has an effect if 'snmpApplyMode' is not set to '1', which is the normal operation. In this case the changed configuration will be applied to the switch (if set to '1') or applied to switch and saved to flash (if set to '2'). This entry is self-clearing.

supplyUsed.name: supplyUsed
supplyUsed.description: If several supplies are possible but not required, this entry decides if an invalid detection leads to an error. An error event can be suppressed if a supply is marked as 'unused'. Hint: If an 'unused' supply is detected as 'valid', it is also automatically marked as 'used'.

supplyStatus.name: supplyStatus
supplyStatus.description: This entry contains the information if the power supply is valid at the moment. An invalid supply will lead to an error event unless it is marked as 'unused'. Hint: If an 'unused' supply is detected as 'valid', it is also automatically marked as 'used'.

pseAvailablePower.name: pseAvailablePower

poepseExtendedVoltage.name: poepseExtendedVoltage
